# ── Compiled binaries ────────────────────────────────────────────
# The default output name from `go build` matches the module name
prd-generator
prd-generator.exe

# Any other compiled output
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binaries
*.test

# ── Go build & test artifacts ────────────────────────────────────
# Output of `go test -coverprofile`
coverage.out
coverage.html

# Benchmark output
*.bench

# ── Environment / secrets ────────────────────────────────────────
# Real secrets — never commit
.env
# .env.example IS committed (it contains no real secrets)

# ── Generated documentation ──────────────────────────────────────
# These are regenerated by `go generate ./...` or `go run ./cmd/docs`.
# Uncomment the lines below if you prefer not to commit the generated files.
# docs/openapi.json
# docs/API_CONTRACTS.md

# ── OS / editor noise ────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
